('Clean Deadlift',
 'glutes', array['hamstrings','lower_back','traps'], array['glutes','hamstrings','lower_back'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Clean-specific deadlift that reinforces the positions of the first and second pull. Setup in clean position: hip-width stance, bar over mid-foot, double overhand grip, hips above parallel, chest tall. Pull the floor away — do not jerk. Bar rises maintaining back angle until above the knee. Then extend hips through maintaining position. Return slowly. Load: typically 110-130% of clean for strength development.',
 'Hips shooting up first (good morning pattern); rounding upper back; jerking bar off floor rather than pressing it away; losing bar position at the hip crease.',
 'strength', array['The floor pushes you: legs press the floor away','Your back angle must not change from lift-off to knee','This is the foundation of your clean — perfect it heavily','Return slowly: teach your body the clean path both ways'],
 array['Clean deadlift with pause at knee','Block pulls at knee height','Clean deadlift from deficit'],
 array['Romanian deadlift for back strength','Conventional deadlift with clean grip','Rack pull for upper position strength'],
