('Jerk Recovery',
 'shoulder', array['core','glutes','triceps'], array['shoulder','core','glutes'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell','squat_rack'], 'advanced', false,
 'From jerk blocks or rack at arm length overhead, set bar in locked out position overhead. Walk forward then step back together. Hold for 3 seconds. Return. Builds confidence overhead and develops the isometric shoulder strength required to hold a maximum jerk. Also used as a heavy overhead stability drill. Load at 105-120% of jerk for strength adaptation.',
 'Not locking elbows completely before adding load; poor head position (head should be through the window); stepping too quickly without stability check; bar drifting forward off centre.',
 'overhead_strength', array['Lock before you step: arms are fully extended first','Head through: chin forward of the bar','Hold the weight: feel it, own it','Bar directly over your base: mid-foot to heel line'],
