('Clean Complex: Power Clean + Front Squat + Jerk',
 'glutes', array['traps','quads','shoulder','core'], array['glutes','traps','quads'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['barbell'], 'advanced', true,
 '1 Power clean + 1 Front squat + 1 Split jerk = 1 rep. Builds the ability to transition between positions and develops the conditioning demand of Olympic lifting competition (multiple movements in sequence). Start at 60-70% of clean max. Key: complete each movement before beginning the next. The front squat between the clean and jerk develops strength in the catch position without adding another clean.',
 'Rushing the transitions; using a weight that compromises any of the three positions; not completing full front squat depth; pressing out on the jerk after fatigue.',
 'complex_training', array['Pause and reset between each movement','Front squat is the hardest part under fatigue: earn it','Your jerk after the front squat is the truest test of your overhead','Complex weight: lighter than your max — perfect reps only'],
