('Pause Clean Below Knee',
 'glutes', array['hamstrings','lower_back','traps'], array['glutes','hamstrings','lower_back'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Clean with a 2-3 second pause just below the knee. Setup as per clean. Pull from floor to 2cm below knee, pause and hold position: back angle maintained, lats engaged, bar over mid-foot, knees still bent. After pause, continue the pull — explosive transition through the knee and into the hip drive. The pause eliminates momentum and forces structural strength in the first-pull position.',
 'Changing back angle during the pause; resting on the quads during the pause (changes angle); rushing out of the pause; losing lat engagement during the pause.',
 'technique_drill', array['Pause is a test: hold perfect position under load','Lats on during the pause: they keep the bar close','Breathe during the pause — you have time','Drive out: after 3 seconds, create controlled explosion'],
 array['Clean with pause at knee','Clean with pause at mid-shin','Full clean with purpose (position consciousness)'],
 array['Clean deadlift to knee with hold','Slow pull clean (no pause, just controlled)','Clean deadlift from floor'],
 array['olympic_lifting','clean','pause','technique_drill','barbell'], array['lower_back_injury'],
