('Tall Snatch',
 'shoulder', array['traps','core','quads'], array['shoulder','traps','core'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['barbell'], 'advanced', false,
 'From standing position with bar at hip height (arm length). No leg drive — pull under and receive in overhead squat using only the arm pull and hip flexibility. Teaches the body to pull itself under the bar actively. Very light weight — technique drill only. Extend up on toes to get bar moving, then immediately pull under into overhead squat.',
 'Using leg drive (defeats the purpose); not moving fast enough to get under the bar; catching without locking arms; using too much weight.',
 'technique_drill', array['No legs: the pull under is the point','Fast turnover: this teaches speed, not strength','Light is right: this is a drill, not a lift','Pull yourself down: think down and through, not up'],
 array['Tall clean (same concept for clean)','Snatch from hang at hip height','Snatch with pause at full extension'],
 array['Hang snatch from hip height','Overhead squat for receiving position','Drop snatch / snatch balance from behind neck'],
 array['olympic_lifting','tall_snatch','technique_drill','speed','barbell'], array['shoulder_instability'],
 'pull', 'sagittal', false, 4, 5, null, 90, true),

('Olympic Lifting Competition Simulation',
