 'RDL-style pull maintaining straight (but not locked) legs. Bar starts from the floor each rep. Much more hamstring-dominant than conventional deadlift. Setup: conventional stance, bar over mid-foot, minimal knee bend. Drive hips back, maintain neutral spine. Bar stays close throughout. The key difference from RDL: the bar returns to the floor completely for each rep (no stretch-shortening off the floor).',
 'Rounding lower back significantly; locking knees (causes knee hyperextension stress); bar drifting from body; using too much weight reducing hamstring control.',
 'powerlifting_accessory', array['Feel the hamstring stretch: if you don''t feel it, you''re not in position','Bar close: drag it up your shins','Soft knee: 10-15° bend prevents knee stress','Lower back neutral: not arched, not rounded — neutral'],
