('Good Morning (Barbell)',
 'lower_back', array['hamstrings','glutes','core'], array['lower_back','hamstrings','glutes'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Bar on upper back (low bar position), shoulder-width or slightly wider stance. Hinge at the hips — do not bend the knees significantly. Lower torso toward parallel with the floor while maintaining a rigid, neutral spine. Drive hips forward to return upright. The good morning is a squat accessory that directly trains the lower back and hamstrings in a position specific to the squat lockout.',
 'Rounding lower back (this makes the good morning dangerous); too much knee bend (converts to an SLDL); going too heavy too quickly; bar sliding forward on the traps.',
 'powerlifting_accessory', array['Hinge — don''t squat: shins stay close to vertical','Rigid spine: your back is a lever, not a spring','Feel your hamstrings stretch: you''re an RDL with the bar on your back','Light first: this movement rewards patience'],
