('Glute Ham Raise (GHD)',
 'hamstrings', array['glutes','lower_back','calves'], array['hamstrings','glutes','lower_back'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['GHD_machine'], 'advanced', false,
 'GHD machine: secure feet, position thighs on pads. Lower body horizontally (eccentric): control the descent over 3-4 seconds. At the bottom, curl legs to return (concentric). The GHD simultaneously trains hip extension and knee flexion — two actions hamstrings perform in athletic movements. One of the most effective posterior chain exercises. Begin with hands-free if strong enough, use arms to push off mat when learning.',
 'Using too much momentum; not controlling the eccentric; not going to full extension at the bottom; skipping this exercise because it''s hard (the difficulty is the point).',
 'powerlifting_accessory', array['Eccentric is everything: 3-second lower','Full extension at bottom: reach for the floor','Curl from the hip and knee simultaneously','Use hands for help at first — wean off them as you get stronger'],
 array['GHD raise with added load (plate on chest)','GHD raise with pause at bottom','GHD sit-up for additional core work'],
 array['Nordic curl for hamstring eccentric','Leg curl machine for knee flexion strength','Romanian deadlift for hip extension'],
