('Zercher Squat',
 'quads', array['glutes','biceps','core','upper_back'], array['quads','glutes','biceps'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell'], 'advanced', true,
 'Bar held in the crooks of the elbows, arms crossed. High-elbow, upright torso squatting pattern. The unusual carry position requires extreme core bracing and upper back tension to prevent forward collapse. Squat to parallel or below. The Zercher position builds the upper back and core strength that carries over to front squats, Olympic lifting front racks, and strongman events.',
 'Bar rolling excessively out of elbows (use elbow sleeves or padding); not keeping elbows lifted; thoracic collapse under the weight; insufficient core bracing.',
 'strength', array['Elbows up: fight to keep them pointed forward','Torso upright: the Zercher position demands it','Brace hard: more core than you think is needed','Pain management: bar-in-elbows is uncomfortable — acknowledge it and work through'],
