('Anderson Squat (From Pins)',
 'quads', array['glutes','hamstrings','core'], array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell','power_rack'], 'advanced', true,
 'Squat starting from the bottom with bar resting on safety pins at parallel. Stand under bar at bottom position. Brace. Drive up from dead stop — no stretch reflex, no momentum. The Anderson squat eliminates the eccentric loading and forces pure concentric strength. Excellent for addressing bottom-of-squat weakness and for athletes returning from knee injury who need bottom-position strength without the eccentric stress.',
 'Positioning incorrectly under the bar (too much forward lean at start); insufficient brace before driving; starting with hips too low reducing leverage; not driving fast from the start.',
