('Spoto Press (2-Inch Bench)',
 'chest', array['triceps','shoulder'], array['chest','triceps','shoulder'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['barbell','bench'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Bench press lowered to 2-3cm above the chest (never touching). Pause in mid-air for 1-2 seconds. Then press. The Spoto press eliminates the touch-and-go advantage, forces extreme pectoral and tricep tension in the bottom range, and trains the hardest part of the bench without the floor (which at least provides feedback). Named after world record holder Eric Spoto.',
