 'Prone on the reverse hyper platform, hips at the edge, legs hanging. Hold handles. Swing legs up and back using glutes and lower back. At the top: hips fully extended. Swing legs back down — the traction of the downswing decompresses the lumbar discs. The reverse hyper trains spinal erectors through a unique arc motion while simultaneously providing therapeutic traction. Invented by Louie Simmons of Westside Barbell.',
