('Sled Push (Sprint)',
 'quads', array['glutes','hamstrings','calves'], array['quads','glutes','hamstrings'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['prowler_sled','weight_plates'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Sprint distance: 20-40m per effort. Load: heavy enough to require effort but not so heavy you stall. Drive explosively: lean forward 45°, short powerful strides, push through both hands. Arms straight, drive from legs. Sprint 20m, rest 90-120s, repeat 6-10 times. The sled push has zero eccentric component — the muscles push but never stretch under load — making it very low DOMS and suitable for daily use.',
 'Standing upright (losing power transfer angle); chopping short steps; using arms to push rather than driving from the legs; insufficient forward lean.',
