('Sled Pull (Rope)',
 'lats', array['biceps','traps','core'], array['lats','biceps','traps'],
 'cardio', 'cardio', array['sled','rope'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Attach a long rope to a loaded sled. Stand facing the sled. Using a hand-over-hand rope pull, drag the sled toward you for 20m. Control the walking speed: each pull should fully stretch the rope. Then push the sled back. The rope pull specifically targets the lats and upper back in a loaded, functional pattern. Great for row strength and grip training without spinal loading.',
 'Using a rope too thin for grip comfort; losing body position (lean back slightly to use body weight); not pulling all the way to the hip at each stroke; letting the rope pile up at feet.',
 'conditioning', array['Lean back: body angle helps the pull','Full stroke: hands from extended to hip','Alternate hands: pull rhythmically','Upper back tight: protect shoulder position'],
 array['Heavy sled rope pull for strength','Sled rope pull seated for pure upper body','Combined sled push-pull circuit'],
 array['Sled drag walking forward','Rope pull on cable machine','Seated cable row'],
 array['sled','rope_pull','upper_body','conditioning','grip','lats'], array['shoulder_impingement'],
 'pull', 'sagittal', false, 6, null, null, 90, true),

('Metabolic Conditioning: "Cindy" (5-10-15)',
 'cardiovascular', array['chest','lats','quads'], array['cardiovascular','chest','lats'],
 'cardio', 'cardio', array['pull_up_bar','bodyweight'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Classic CrossFit benchmark. 20-minute AMRAP: 5 pull-ups, 10 push-ups, 15 air squats. Score: total rounds + partial. Average scores: beginner 5-7 rounds, intermediate 12-15, advanced 20+. Scaling: banded pull-ups, knee push-ups, reduce reps. "Mary" variation: 5 HSPU, 10 single-leg squats, 15 pull-ups (more advanced). Tracks fitness over months — retest every 6-8 weeks.',
