('Wall Ball Shot',
 'quads', array['glutes','shoulder','core'], array['quads','glutes','shoulder'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['medicine_ball','wall'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Hold medicine ball at chest (6-9kg). Squat to full depth. Drive up explosively, throw ball to target on wall (3m for women, 3.5m for men in competition). Catch ball at chest. Immediately squat again. The continuous motion develops lower body power, upper body pushing strength, and cardiovascular conditioning simultaneously. Staple in CrossFit competitions.',
 'Not reaching full squat depth; throwing with arms only (no leg drive); catching ball at wrong height leading to timing issues; letting ball bounce rather than catching it cleanly.',
 'conditioning', array['Full squat: crease below parallel before the drive','Drive from the legs: the throw starts in your hips','Catch and immediately sit: no pause at the top','Target: the ball should hit at or above target height every time'],
