('Box Jump Burpee Complex',
 'glutes', array['quads','chest','shoulder'], array['glutes','quads','chest'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['plyo_box','bodyweight'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Burpee to box jump. Stand behind box. Drop to burpee (chest to floor). Jump feet in, stand, immediately jump onto box, land in full squat, stand tall, step down. Repeat. Alternatively: lateral burpee over box. 5 rounds of 10 reps is a challenging conditioning set. The combination of horizontal push (burpee) and vertical jump (box jump) creates full-body metabolic demand.',
 'Landing heavily on the box with stiff legs; jumping down instead of stepping down (increases injury risk when fatigued); rushing the burpee chest touch; not achieving full extension at the top of box jump.',
 'conditioning', array['Chest to floor on the burpee: full range counts','Jump to the box: don''t hop timidly — commit','Land softly: absorb at the hips and knees','Step down: don''t jump down when fatigued (risk increases)'],
