 'Concurrent training: running and lifting in a superset. Format: 400m run at 80% effort, immediately: 15 thrusters at 40kg (men) / 25kg (women). Rest 2 minutes. 6 rounds. The cardiovascular demand of the run then immediately requiring muscular strength tests neuromuscular performance under fatigue. Mimics the demands of obstacle course racing and functional fitness competitions.',
