('Turkish Get-Up (Single Bell)',
 'shoulder', array['core','glutes','hip_flexors','quads'], array['shoulder','core','glutes'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['kettlebell'], 'advanced', true,
 'Start lying on back, kettlebell pressed in one hand, arm straight. Follow the 7-step TGU: (1) Roll to propped elbow. (2) Press to hand. (3) Hip bridge. (4) Sweep rear leg back to half-kneeling. (5) Kneel tall. (6) Stand. Then reverse each step to return to lying. The TGU tests and develops shoulder stability, core control, and full-body coordination in a slow, intentional movement. The kettlebell must remain vertical throughout.',
 'Rushing the steps; losing vertical arm position (most common); not bracing through each position change; using too heavy a weight before mastering with light bell or shoe; poor hip bridge height.',
 'functional_strength', array['Eyes on the bell: where your eyes go, the bell follows','Arm vertical: imagine a glass of water on your fist','Each position is its own mini-exercise: pause and own it','Reverse precisely: the way down is as important as the way up'],
 array['Weighted TGU with heavy bell','TGU windmill combination','TGU with press at the top for overhead strength'],
 array['TGU with shoe balanced on fist (no weight)','TGU with light dumbbell','Partial TGU (floor to seated only)'],
 array['kettlebell','turkish_get_up','shoulder_stability','core','full_body','functional'], array['shoulder_instability','wrist_injury'],
 'mixed', 'multi', true, 3, 5, null, 60, true),

('Clean and Press (Barbell) Conditioning Complex',
 'glutes', array['shoulder','traps','quads'], array['glutes','shoulder','traps'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['barbell'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Power clean + strict press or push press. Conditioning format: 5 complexes per minute x 10 minutes EMOM, or 10 sets of 3 for strength-conditioning. The clean develops explosive posterior chain power; the press develops overhead strength. Together they create a full-body conditioning stimulus. Weight: 50-65% of clean max. Strict press version trains pure overhead strength; push press adds leg drive.',
 'Pressing before establishing front rack position; using too heavy a weight limiting the clean technique; rushing reps within the complex; not resetting at each position.',
 'conditioning', array['Full clean first: front rack, elbows up','Press from power position: feet set, core braced','No rush between movements: quick but controlled','Weight should allow clean technique to stay intact'],
 array['Clean and jerk (progression from push press)','Heavy single clean and press','Complex: clean + front squat + push press'],
 array['Power clean only','Push press only for overhead development','Hang clean + dumbbell press'],
 array['HIIT','clean_press','conditioning','barbell','complex','full_body'], array['shoulder_instability'],
