('Double Under Jump Rope',
 'calves', array['shoulder','core','cardiovascular'], array['calves','shoulder','core'],
 'cardio', 'cardio', array['jump_rope'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Jump rope where the rope passes under the feet twice per jump. Requires: (1) Taller jump than single unders. (2) Faster wrist rotation (not arm circles — only wrists). (3) Relaxed shoulders. Learning: 1 single, 1 double, 1 single pattern first. Then: 3 singles + 1 double. Finally: consecutive doubles. Common CrossFit workout rep schemes: 50 unbroken doubles as a benchmark.',
