('Sandbag Conditioning Circuit',
 'glutes', array['core','shoulder','quads'], array['glutes','core','shoulder'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['sandbag'], 'intermediate', true,
 'Sandbag circuit (each movement for 40s on / 20s rest): (1) Sandbag shouldering (pick up, put on shoulder). (2) Sandbag bear hug carry 20m. (3) Sandbag squat. (4) Sandbag overhead press. (5) Sandbag burpee (over the bag). (6) Sandbag clean. 3-4 rounds total. Sandbag training develops grip strength, core stability, and the ability to move awkward loads — directly applicable to real-world and functional fitness.',
 'Poor lifting mechanics with the unstable load; grip failing before cardiovascular capacity; not adapting to the shifting weight of the sandbag; using a heavy bag before mastering technique with lighter.',
 'conditioning', array['Sandbag shifts: brace your core harder than with a barbell','Grip the bag aggressively: it will move on you','Functional strength: this is what real loads feel like','The awkwardness is the point: it makes you stronger in more positions'],
 array['HYROX sandbag lunges competition standard','Sandbag carry for distance','Sandbag complex with barbell equivalent loads'],
