('Farmer Carry Progressive Loading',
 'traps', array['forearm','core','glutes'], array['traps','forearm','core'],
 'strength', 'cardio', array['farmer_carry_implements','dumbbells','kettlebells'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Carry heavy implements for distance or time. Hold dumbbells, kettlebells, or farmer carry handles at each side. Walk with tall posture, short strides, shoulders back, core braced. Protocol: 4x30m carries with 60-90s rest between. Progress: increase load weekly. Competition distances: 25-50m with maximum load. The farmer carry builds grip strength, trap strength, and walking core stability.',
 'Leaning forward (losing core position); not maintaining shoulder retraction (causes trap fatigue from poor position); walking with too wide a stance; running with the carries (increases swinging and fall risk).',
 'loaded_carry', array['Stand tall: the weight wants to pull you forward, fight it','Short steps: shuffle, don''t stride','Shoulders back and down: retract, don''t let them elevate','Grip white-knuckle tight: your grip is your weakest link'],
