 'Kettlebell sport snatch: one-arm, 10-minute set, one hand switch. Swing bell between legs and behind hip, drive with hips, bell rises up the arm (not a swing to front and flip), receive at lockout overhead. The bell should travel up the arm path to the overhead position — not a swing and press. Competition: maximum reps in 10 minutes. Elite athletes: 200+ reps in 10 minutes with 24kg.',
 'Pressing out at the top (not using momentum from the flip); swinging too far forward (increases shoulder injury risk); hyperextending the lower back; poor hand insertion (catching the bell too late).',
 'kettlebell_sport', array['Backswing deep: bell travels behind the hips','The flip: the bell rotates around your hand, not over it','Insert hand early: meet the bell, don''t chase it','Lockout: completely straight arm before descending'],
 array['10-minute kettlebell snatch test','Double kettlebell snatch','Progressive set length 3 → 5 → 7 → 10 min'],
 array['Single rep KB snatch technique focus','One-arm swing for hip hinge mastery','Dumbbell snatch for motion pattern'],
