('Kettlebell Jerk (Double)',
 'shoulder', array['glutes','quads','core'], array['shoulder','glutes','quads'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['kettlebell'], 'advanced', false,
 'Double kettlebell jerk (two bells). Both bells in rack position. Two-phase: first dip — shallow, simultaneous; second dip (squat or split) — pull body under both bells as they rise from the initial drive. Lock out both arms simultaneously. Return to rack. The double jerk demands exceptional rack position symmetry and overhead stability. Competition lift in GS (Girevoy Sport).',
 'Unequal dip depth causing asymmetrical drive; not completing full lockout on both arms simultaneously; insufficient hip drive reducing jerk efficiency; bells hitting face (keep elbows in front).',
 'kettlebell_sport', array['Symmetry: both bells must move identically','First dip drives: legs do 80% of the work','Second dip: drop under both bells together','Lockout: stacked from wrist to shoulder — fully vertical arms'],
 array['Double jerk 10-minute competition set','Double jerk with increasing load','Double jerk into push press transition'],
 array['Single arm jerk for mechanics','Push press double for overhead prep','Rack position endurance holds'],
 array['kettlebell_sport','double_jerk','overhead','competition','conditioning'], array['shoulder_instability'],
