('Kettlebell Swing (Russian vs American)',
 'glutes', array['hamstrings','lower_back','core'], array['glutes','hamstrings','lower_back'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['kettlebell'], 'beginner', false,
 'Russian swing: bell swings to eye-level maximum. American swing: bell continues overhead to full lockout. Russian swing: safer, generates same posterior chain power, allows heavier loading. Both start the same: hip hinge with bell between legs, explosive hip snap, bell rises. On Russian: stop at eye level with lat tension. On American: continue to overhead with full arm lockout. CrossFit uses American; sport and conditioning generally uses Russian.',
 'Squatting the swing (it is a hip hinge, not a squat); rounding lower back; using arms to lift (they guide, don''t pull); the bell should feel weightless at the top — if it feels heavy, the hip snap was insufficient.',
 'conditioning', array['HINGE: push hips back aggressively before the snap','Snap: hips drive forward violently, glutes squeeze','Bell guides: arms are attached to the bell, not lifting it','Lat tension at top: bell should feel light'],
 array['Single arm swing for instability challenge','Swing into clean for complex','Heavy double swing'],
 array['Romanian deadlift for hip hinge pattern','Hip hinge with band for force feedback','Swing with lighter bell for technique'],
 array['kettlebell','swing','hip_hinge','glutes','conditioning','explosive'], array['lower_back_injury_acute'],
 'explosive', 'sagittal', false, 4, 20, null, 60, true),

('Kettlebell Goblet Squat',
 'quads', array['glutes','core','hip_flexors'], array['quads','glutes','core'],
 'strength', 'strength', array['kettlebell'], 'beginner', true,
 'Hold kettlebell by horns at chest height (goblet position). Squat to full depth — elbows track inside knees as you descend. Upright torso. At the bottom: elbows press knees open, creating hip external rotation for depth. Stand tall. The goblet squat is the best squat teaching tool: the anterior load forces an upright torso, the bell provides counterbalance, and the elbows cue knee tracking.',
 'Bell drooping forward at bottom (losing torso position); feet too narrow limiting depth; elbows not pressing knees open; using goblet squat weight as a limit rather than a teaching tool.',
 'strength', array['Chest tall: the bell wants to pull you forward, fight it','Elbows open knees: push them out at the bottom','Heels down: weight through heels, not toes','Own the bottom: pause there and feel the hip opening'],
 array['Goblet squat with heavier bell','Goblet squat with pause and press at bottom','Progressed to barbell front squat'],
 array['Box goblet squat to depth marker','Air squat for basic pattern first','Assisted squat holding TRX'],
 array['kettlebell','goblet_squat','squat','teaching_tool','beginner','strength'], array['knee_injury','hip_impingement'],
 'push', 'sagittal', false, 4, 10, null, 60, true),

('Kettlebell Clean (Single Arm)',
 'glutes', array['traps','forearm','core'], array['glutes','traps','forearm'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['kettlebell'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Single-arm kettlebell clean to rack position. Swing bell between legs, drive hips, guide bell up the arm in a corkscrew path. The bell rotates around the hand — it does not swing up and over. At the rack: bell rests on forearm, wrist straight, elbow resting on hip. The path: backswing → hip drive → bell travels up inner arm → rotate over hand → land in rack. Avoiding the crash is the primary skill to master.',
 'Swinging bell out in front and letting it crash over the hand; elbow not contacting the hip in rack (holding the bell up with muscle); wrist bending in rack; curling the bell (using bicep).',
 'kettlebell_technique', array['The bell travels up your arm: it doesn''t swing','Rotate your hand early: meet the bell on the way up','Rack: elbow touches hip — you rest the bell, you don''t carry it','Wrist straight in rack: pressure is on the forearm'],
 array['Double kettlebell clean','Clean to press combination','Kettlebell clean and squat complex'],
 array['Hip hinge with swing for hip drive pattern','KB deadlift for basic hip hinge','One-arm band pull for arm path pattern'],
 array['kettlebell','clean','rack_position','technique','explosive'], array['wrist_injury','elbow_injury'],
