 'Bending the elbow during the movement; rotating at the spine instead of hinging at the hip; looking down instead of at the bell (maintaining eye contact with bell is essential); insufficient hamstring flexibility forcing spinal rounding.',
 'functional_strength', array['Eyes on the bell: always','Arm locked: it is a vertical pole attached to the ground through your hand','Hinge, don''t rotate: your hip moves, your spine stays neutral','If you lose the bell overhead — it is too heavy'],
