('Kettlebell Complex: Swing + Clean + Press + Squat',
 'glutes', array['shoulder','core','quads'], array['glutes','shoulder','core'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['kettlebell'], 'advanced', true,
 '4-movement kettlebell complex, one hand: 1 swing → 1 clean to rack → 1 press → 1 front squat. All with the same bell without putting it down. 5 reps per side = 1 round. 4-6 rounds with 2 min rest. This complex covers: posterior chain (swing), pull mechanics (clean), overhead strength (press), and lower body (squat). The transition between movements tests efficiency and technique under accumulating fatigue.',
 'Using too heavy a bell (every movement must be technically sound); putting the bell down within the complex; rushing the press (technique deteriorates fastest under fatigue); swinging without hip drive.',
