 'Single-arm swing to overhead in one movement. Backswing between legs, hip drive, bell rises up the arm, rotate hand under bell, punch overhead to lockout in one fluid arc. The bell should not loop out in front — it travels up the forearm to the overhead position. Single arm, alternating hands. The snatch is the most efficient test of hip power, grip, and shoulder stability in one movement.',
 'Looping the bell out in front causing shoulder stress; not using the hip drive (arm press); crashing the bell over the hand at lockout; not locking out elbow and shoulder fully.',
