 'Conventional hip hinge with kettlebell between feet. Bell on floor. Hip-width stance, bell between feet. Hinge at hips, push shins forward slightly to reach bell, neutral spine. Drive hips forward to stand. Lower with control. The kettlebell deadlift is the best entry-level deadlift variation — the bell''s central position (between the feet) is more forgiving than a barbell and teaches the hip hinge with lower injury risk.',
 'Rounding lower back; squatting the pull (bell too far forward); not achieving full lockout at the top; jerking the bell rather than pressing the floor; looking up excessively.',
