('Kettlebell Flow (Movement Sequence)',
 'cardiovascular', array['shoulder','core','glutes'], array['cardiovascular','shoulder','core'],
 'cardio', 'explosive', array['kettlebell'], 'advanced', false,
 'Continuous movement flow without putting bell down. Example sequence: Swing x5, Clean x1, Press x1, Front squat x1, Snatch x1, Overhead hold 3s, Lower to swing x5. All one bell, one hand, flowing. 4-5 minutes per side. Kettlebell flow combines all major KB movements into an intuitive sequence — develops timing, efficiency, and conditioning simultaneously.',
 'Forcing rote sequences (flow should be intuitive); too heavy a bell limiting movement quality; not allowing rests within the flow when needed; forgetting to include downward movements (everything can''t go up).',
