 'Two kettlebells cleaned to rack position. Squat to full depth maintaining the rack — elbows forward, bells on forearms. The double front rack creates greater core and thoracic extension demand than a barbell front squat. The front load forces an upright torso. Stand fully at top. An excellent squat variation that also trains the rack position endurance critical for Olympic lifting and kettlebell sport.',
