('Kettlebell Tater (Deadlift + Swing + Snatch)',
 'glutes', array['traps','shoulder','hamstrings'], array['glutes','traps','shoulder'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['kettlebell'], 'advanced', true,
 'Single bell complex: 1 deadlift → 1 swing → 1 clean → 1 press. Flowing without stopping. Deadlift teaches the safe setup, swing adds hip power, clean develops the rack, press completes overhead. This is a complete posterior chain and pressing circuit in one seamless movement. 5 reps per side, 5 rounds, 2 min rest. A beginner-to-intermediate complex for learning to chain movements.',
 'Not making a full stop between the deadlift and swing (safety issue — the deadlift position must be established); using too much weight; confusing the hip hinge timing between movements.',
 'complex_training', array['Deadlift: full setup and pull, THEN swing','Each movement must be complete before the next begins','Same bell: choose weight for your weakest movement','Breathe in the back-swing: there is a natural pause there'],
 array['Speed through the complex as conditioning','Extended complex (add front squat after press)','Heavier bell reducing reps'],
 array['3-movement complex without press','Deadlift + swing only for hip hinge pattern','Individual movements in sequence with rest between'],
 array['kettlebell','complex','deadlift','swing','clean','press','beginner_complex'], array['lower_back_injury'],
