('Muscle-Up (Bar)',
 'lats', array['chest','triceps','core','shoulder'], array['lats','chest','triceps'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['pull_up_bar'], 'advanced', true,
 'Pull-up transitioning into a dip above the bar. Start with false grip or regular grip. Pull explosively, drive elbows behind you at the top of the pull, then simultaneously push hands down and lever body over the bar. End in straight-arm support above the bar. The transition (from pull to push) is the most difficult part. Training: (1) Jumping muscle-up for pattern. (2) Pull-up to chest. (3) Negative from top. Then combine.',
 'Insufficient pull-up strength base (need 10+ pull-ups before attempting); kipping without understanding the mechanics (kipping should add to strength, not replace it); diving head forward rather than pushing hips up; not developing the transition specifically.',
 'gymnastics_strength', array['Pull your chest to the bar first: height is everything','The turn: elbows go back AND you rotate hips up','Push over the bar: press down as you transition','Straight arm support: lock out completely above the bar'],
 array['Ring muscle-up (more wrist-friendly)','Weighted muscle-up','Consecutive muscle-up reps for conditioning'],
 array['High chest pull-up (transition prep)','Pull-up to transition with band assistance','Muscle-up negative from top position'],
