('Planche (Progression)',
 'shoulder', array['chest','triceps','core'], array['shoulder','chest','triceps'],
 'strength', 'isometric', array['parallel_bars','floor','push_up_handles'], 'advanced', false,
 'The planche: both hands on the floor, body horizontal with no leg support. Progressions: tuck planche → advanced tuck → straddle → full planche. Start with tuck: knees to chest, body leans forward of hands, protract shoulders aggressively. All progressions: shoulders must be ahead of the hands (forward lean), scapulae protracted (pushed forward), wrists extended and loaded. Bands and lean training are the primary training tools.',
 'Insufficient wrist strength/flexibility (highest injury risk for planche training); not protracting scapulae (must push hands through the floor); underestimating the shoulder lean required; rushing progressions.',
 'gymnastics_strength', array['Lean forward: your shoulders must be ahead of your wrists','Protract: push the floor apart and round your upper back slightly','Straight arms: always — planche requires elbow lockout','Patience: the planche takes 6-18 months of dedicated training'],
 array['Straddle planche 5s hold','Full planche push-up','Planche maltese combination'],
 array['Tuck planche lean holds','Pseudo planche push-up for wrist and shoulder prep','Planche lean against wall (band-assisted)'],
