 'Push-up in a handstand position against a wall. From wall handstand: lower head toward floor (strictly: head to floor) then press back to lockout. Range of motion: full overhead press range but inverted. Scaling: pike push-up → elevated pike → box HSPU → strict HSPU. Competition standard: head touches the floor at the bottom. Kipping HSPU: uses a hip pop to assist the press (CrossFit competition standard).',
 'Flaring elbows excessively (reduce to avoid shoulder impingement); not achieving full lockout at the top; kipping without strict capacity developed first; head placement too far from hands.',
