 'strength', 'isometric', array['parallel_bars','push_up_handles','floor'], 'intermediate', false,
 'Sit on the floor (or support on bars/handles). Press hands into the floor, straight arms, lift body off the floor with legs extended parallel to the ground forming an L-shape. Progression: tuck L-sit → one-leg extended → full L-sit. Full L-sit: both legs horizontal, toes pointed, arms straight. Hold for time. The L-sit is the most fundamental gymnastics skill that transfers to every other gymnastics movement.',
