('Bar Kip and Kipping Pull-Up',
 'lats', array['core','shoulder','hip_flexors'], array['lats','core','shoulder'],
 'strength', 'explosive', array['pull_up_bar'], 'intermediate', false,
 'The kip uses a whole-body swing to generate momentum for efficient pull-ups in gymnastics and fitness. The hollow-arch swing: (1) Hollow body (dish position — hips forward, arched back). (2) Arch body (superhero position — hips back, chest forward). (3) Drive hips forward and pull simultaneously at the peak of the forward swing. Head goes back, chin over bar. Kipping allows more volume and speed than strict pull-ups — valuable in CrossFit competition.',
 'Kipping without any strict pull-up ability (injury risk without base strength); poor hollow-arch swing mechanics; chin not clearing the bar; kipping to mask strength deficit permanently.',
 'gymnastics_skill', array['Hollow-arch is the engine: perfect the swing first','Drive hips: at the peak of the forward swing, that is when you pull','Full range: chin over bar every rep','Kipping amplifies strength: it doesn''t replace it'],
 array['Butterfly kip for even faster cycling','Kipping chest-to-bar pull-up','Kipping muscle-up from kipping pull-up'],
 array['Strict pull-up for base strength (5 minimum before kipping)','Hanging hollow-arch swing without pulling','Jumping pull-up for pattern'],
 array['calisthenics','kipping_pull_up','gymnastics','CrossFit','efficiency','swing'], array['shoulder_instability'],
