 'Pull-up to the top, then shift body sideways — travel from one hand to the other while maintaining chin-over-bar height. Right, center, left, center = 1 rep. The lateral shift requires the lats and arm flexors to maintain height while transferring weight between sides — developing unilateral pulling strength. Prerequisite: 10+ strict pull-ups.',
