 'Evidence-based eccentric hamstring training. Progressive protocol (4-week blocks): Week 1: 2x5 (3-second lower). Week 2: 3x6. Week 3: 3x8. Week 4: 4x8. Rest 48h between sessions. At the bottom, use hands to push up (assistance) then control the next lowering. The Nordic curl has the highest evidence base for hamstring strain prevention in sport (reduces injury rate 51% in RCT evidence).',
